description = Retrieve, capture, or refresh distilled context-engineering knowledge — managing what goes in a model's context window, why long contexts degrade (lost-in-the-middle, context rot, distractors), and the write/select/compress/isolate operations that counter it. Use when deciding what to put in context, debugging long-context quality, or looking up or saving a context-engineering principle — not when composing the instruction's wording, exemplars, or output format (that is prompt-engineering), nor when designing a tool's contract or what it returns (that is tool-design).
